contentrichtext.text: '''Moira''' may refer to: * [[Moira (fate)]], one of the three Fates, known collectively as [[Moirai]] * [[Moira (portion)]], an ancient Greek word referring to a portion of the whole ==Places== * [[Moira, Achaea]], a village in Greece * [[Moira, County Down]], Northern Ireland town ** [[Moira railway station]], Moira, Northern Ireland * [[Moira, Goa]], a village in India * [[Moira, Leicestershire]], English village ** [[Moira Furnace]], nineteenth century iron-making blast furnace * [[County of Moira]], Victoria, Australia * [[Division of Moira]], Victoria, Australia, an Electoral Division * [[Shire of Moira]], a local government area in Victoria, Australia * [[Moira, New South Wales]], Australian rural community * [[Moira, New York]], American town * [[Moira, Ontario]], Canadian unincorporated area * [[Moira Lake]], Ontario, Canada * [[Moira River]], Ontario, Canada * [[638 Moira]], an asteroid ==Other== * [[Moira (given name)]] * [[Earl of Moira]], an Irish title * [[Moira (military)]], a Greek military formation * [[HMS Moira (1805)|HMS ''Moira'' (1805)]], British Royal Navy schooner * {{SS|Moira}}, a Greek coaster in service during 1966 * [[Moira (album)|''Moira'' (album)]], a story album by the Japanese musical group Sound Horizon * [[Moira (genus)]], a genus of [[echinoderm]]s {{disambig|geo}}
